--- !u!114 &34317786
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 34317779}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 9c3218af31b9a124b9c0befbc3fec8d2, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  allEmails:
  - id: corporate_start
    sender: 'Your Boss  '
    subject: Welcome, New Manager!
    preview: First of all, I'd like to...
    body: "Well hello there, intern! Welcome to your first day at [park name]. We\u2019re
      happy to have some fresh meat after last year\u2019s escaped goblin incident.
      Ah, but that\u2019s nothing for you to worry about! By now we\u2019ve managed
      to wrangle all our escapees back to their rightful places. Probably.\r\nAnyways,
      as you may know, taking magical creatures from the wild is generally illegal,
      except in cases of rescue and rehabilitation. Of course there are channels
      to get around that\u2026 but we\u2019ll wait to have that discussion until
      I\u2019m sure you can keep your mouth shut. In any case, that means that the
      creatures we take in most likely have injuries and diseases you\u2019ll have
      to treat.\r\nOur first addition to the park is a young Ryufuku, rescued by
      some fishing boats after a storm. This one has already been mostly treated,
      so you\u2019ll only have to worry about the day-to-day care. We\u2019ve already
      constructed your first habitat, which can house up to four creatures. Your
      first step is to release the dragon from its shipping container into the habitat.\r\nYou\u2019ll
      be able to oversee the habitats through the security cameras, and once you\u2019ve
      navigated to the habitat you want your creature to be placed in, you can click
      on it to slot the creature in.\r\n\r\n[Creature attached to email. Player clicks
      to add to inventory]\r\n\n\nWe look forward to hearing back from you about
      your success!\n\n\nYour Boss"
  - id: conservation_m1
    sender: 'Your Boss  '
    subject: Feeding the Fishes
    preview: First of all, I'd like to...
    body: "I see your first creature has been released into their habitat. Well done!
      Now that they\u2019re on display, the customers will start arriving at the
      park to see what we have to offer. The greater the quantity and rarity of the
      creatures we have on display, the more money we earn in admission fees at the
      end of the day. Admission fees alone won\u2019t make us rich, but they\u2019re
      enough to offset some of the costs in caring for the creatures.\r\nYour major
      care costs will be food and healing items. You can find those at the store,
      along with additional habitats once you\u2019re ready to expand.\r\nAs for
      the sort of food you should get\u2026 how should I know? Each creature has
      a certain weight of food they want to eat per day. Too much and they\u2019ll
      become overweight, too little and they\u2019ll get malnourished. They also
      have a certain amount of each food type that they need to eat per day. Anything
      over that will only add weight.\r\nYou\u2019ll mix the food once per day, and
      feed mixes are shared across creatures in the habitat. The correct food ratios
      are consistent across members of a species, but you\u2019ll have to experiment
      to find out what they are. Or you might see if you can get in touch with the
      Research Lab. They\u2019ll be able to find out how you should feed your creatures\u2026
      for a price, of course.\r\nWhy don\u2019t you go ahead and feed your Ryufuku
      now? I\u2019ll give you some spending money to help you out.\r\n\r\n[Player
      gets $15000]\r\n"
